stories_text_raw:
Here is the list of user stories derived from the Python code, formatted as requested:

As a user, I want to create a submission, so that I can track my work in progress.  
As a user, I want to update the publish status of my submission, so that I can track its approval progress.  
As a user, I want to add errors to my submission, so that I can document issues that need resolution.  
As a user, I want to add warnings to my submission, so that I can document potential concerns without blocking progress.  
As a data manager, I want to process deletions for a specific date, so that I can maintain data cleanliness.  
As a data manager, I want to sync D1 file generation with FPDS data load, so that my data remains consistent.  
As a data manager, I want to update the validation rule table, so that data integrity is maintained.  
As a data manager, I want to manage D Files cache, so that duplicate generation requests are prevented.  
As a UI designer, I want to redesign the Resources page, so that it follows the latest design standards.  
As a UI designer, I want to report user testing results to agencies, so that they can provide feedback.  
As a UI designer, I want to manage design approvals for pages, so that design changes are properly tracked.  
As a submission manager, I want to lock submissions during publishing, so that concurrent modifications are prevented.  
As a file processor, I want to validate FABS submission files, so that data quality is ensured.  
As a file processor, I want to generate D Files from FABS and FPDS data, so that reports can be created.  
As an administrator, I want to set user permissions, so that access control is enforced.  
As an administrator, I want to check user permissions, so that unauthorized actions are prevented.  
As a data analyst, I want to load historical FPDS data, so that I can perform trend analysis.  
As a data analyst, I want to load historical FABS data, so that I can perform historical comparisons.  
As a developer, I want to configure logging, so that application activity is properly recorded.  
As a system operator, I want to run the main application, so that all components work together as designed.
